766
00:52:49,886 --> 00:52:52,846
Brooks, how long have you been librarian?

767
00:52:52,931 --> 00:52:58,101
Oh...I come here in '05,
and they made me librarian in 1912.

768
00:52:58,186 --> 00:53:01,563
And in all that time,
have you ever had an assistant?

769
00:53:01,648 --> 00:53:04,233
No. No, not much to it, really.

770
00:53:04,317 --> 00:53:06,235
Well, why me? Why now?

771
00:53:06,319 --> 00:53:07,819
I don't know,

772
00:53:07,904 --> 00:53:11,240
but it'll be nice to have some company
down here for a change.

773
00:53:11,241 --> 00:53:13,325
<font color="#808080">HADLEY :</font> Dufresne!

774
00:53:22,627 --> 00:53:24,711
That's him. That's the one.

775
00:53:32,262 --> 00:53:33,553
I'm Dekins.

776
00:53:33,638 --> 00:53:36,098
<font color="#ff00ff">(Nervously)</font> I was er...

777
00:53:36,182 --> 00:53:40,185
thinking about maybe setting up
some kind of trust fund for my kids' educations.

778
00:53:42,522 --> 00:53:43,981
Oh...

779
00:53:44,065 --> 00:53:45,732
I see.

780
00:53:47,193 --> 00:53:49,069
Well, erm...

781
00:53:50,446 --> 00:53:51,989
..why don't we have a seat,

782
00:53:52,073 --> 00:53:54,157
and talk it over?

783
00:53:56,703 --> 00:53:59,621
Brooks,
do you have a piece of paper and a pencil?

784
00:54:11,092 --> 00:54:12,801
Thanks.

785
00:54:12,885 --> 00:54:14,553
So...

786
00:54:15,805 --> 00:54:18,307
Mr. Dekins...

787
00:54:18,391 --> 00:54:22,853
And then Andy says to Mr. Dekins,
"Do you want your sons to go to Harvard,

788
00:54:22,937 --> 00:54:25,063
- or Yale?"
- He didn't say that?

789
00:54:25,148 --> 00:54:27,816
As God is my witness, he did!

790
00:54:27,900 --> 00:54:31,278
Dekins just blinked for a second.
Then he laughed himself silly.

791
00:54:31,362 --> 00:54:33,238
And afterwards he shook Andy's hand.

792
00:54:33,323 --> 00:54:34,698
My ass!

793
00:54:34,782 --> 00:54:35,991
Shook his hand.

794
00:54:36,075 --> 00:54:39,036
Hell, I...I near soiled myself! <font color="#ff00ff">(Laughs)</font>

795
00:54:39,120 --> 00:54:43,332
All Andy needed was a suit and a tie
and a little jiggly hula girl on his desk,

796
00:54:43,416 --> 00:54:44,750
and he would have been:

797
00:54:44,834 --> 00:54:46,376
"Mr. Dufresne, if you please"!

798
00:54:46,461 --> 00:54:48,211
Making a few friends, Andy?

799
00:54:49,255 --> 00:54:51,214
I wouldn't say "friends".

800
00:54:51,299 --> 00:54:55,302
I'm a convicted murderer
who provides sound financial planning.

801
00:54:55,386 --> 00:54:57,721
It's a wonderful pet to have.

802
00:54:57,805 --> 00:54:59,723
Got you out of the laundry, though.

803
00:54:59,807 --> 00:55:02,017
Well, it might do more than that.

804
00:55:02,101 --> 00:55:05,103
How about expanding the library?
Get some new books in there.

805
00:55:05,188 --> 00:55:07,898
If you're gonna ask for something,
ask for a pool table.

806
00:55:07,982 --> 00:55:10,442
- Right.
- How do you expect to do that?

807
00:55:10,526 --> 00:55:15,781
I mean, get new books in here,
Mr. Dufresne, if you please?

808
00:55:15,865 --> 00:55:17,616
Ask the Warden for funds.

809
00:55:17,700 --> 00:55:18,950
<font color="#ff00ff">(Laughter)</font>

810
00:55:19,035 --> 00:55:22,329
Son, son. Six wardens
have been through here in my tenure,

811
00:55:22,413 --> 00:55:26,041
and I've learned one immutable, universal truth.

812
00:55:26,125 --> 00:55:27,834
Not one of them born...

813
00:55:27,835 --> 00:55:32,798
whose asshole wouldn't pucker up tighter than
a snare drum when you asked them for funds.

814
00:55:32,882 --> 00:55:35,175
The budget's stretched thin, as it is.

815
00:55:35,259 --> 00:55:36,510
I see.

816
00:55:36,594 --> 00:55:40,138
Perhaps I could write to the State Senate
and request funds from them.

817
00:55:40,223 --> 00:55:44,601
As far as they're concerned, there's only three
ways to spend money when it comes to prisons:

818
00:55:44,685 --> 00:55:46,770
more walls, more bars and more guards.

819
00:55:46,854 --> 00:55:51,274
